Package tradedatacorp.smelter.lexical.binary

Interface BinaryLexical<RefinedT>

Type Parameters:
RefinedT - A singular Datapoint object. Each data point is exactly the same number of bits concatenated together.
All Superinterfaces:
Lexical
All Known Implementing Classes:
Original
public interface BinaryLexical<RefinedT> extends Lexical
An interface for taking objects and translating to and from binary format (serializing and deserializing). This interface has a header that represents the metadata about the data points. There is one header and one or more data.

    • getBinaryData

      boolean[][] getBinaryData(RefinedT singleData)
      Returns a 2D boolean array representing a singular data point.
      Parameters:
      singleData - A datapoint Object that will be converted to a 2D boolean Array.
      Returns:
      2D boolean array. Each element (the first dimension) represents a data field for that specific data point. This is the reverse process of getRefinedData(boolean[][] singleBinaryData).
